{"id":14881843,"mediaExerciseId":"524d3988-d86b-40b0-bcb5-4c90680aafff","exerciseName":"1","chapterName":"23","chapterTitle":"Enterprise Risk Management","groupId":612489,"groupTitle":"Minicase Questions","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":789,"solutions":[{"id":6028909,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"For this, we will use the formula for the computation of monthly mortgage which is given as:\n\n$$\\begin{aligned}\n\\text{Monthly mortgage}&=\\dfrac{P \\times R}{1-(1+R)^{-n}}\n\\end{aligned}$$\n\nWhere,\n\n$$\\begin{aligned}\nP&=\\text{Amount of loan}\\\\\nR&=\\text{Periodic interest rate}\\\\\nn&=\\text{number of periods}\n\\end{aligned}$$\n","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":376,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/16/e69522ec2461ca14fd0f2cca3367b4ee/a6457da5ea83b98b30efe6987a3c7849/lateximg_large.png","width":996},"regular":{"height":188,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/16/e69522ec2461ca14fd0f2cca3367b4ee/a6457da5ea83b98b30efe6987a3c7849/lateximg.png","width":499}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"For this problem, we will use $P=\\$400,000$ with an interest rate of $6\\%$ which translates to a $0.5\\%$ monthly periodic rate. Moreover, we will use $n=12\\ \\text{months} \\times 25\\ \\text{years} = 300$\n\nSubstituting these values to the formula, we will get:\n\n$$\\begin{aligned}\n\\text{Monthly mortgage}&=\\dfrac{\\$400,000 \\times 0.005}{1-(1+0.005)^{-300}}\\\\\n&=\\$2,577.21\n\\end{aligned}$$\n\nThe monthly payment will be $\\$2,577.21$\n","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":347,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/16/e69522ec2461ca14fd0f2cca3367b4ee/901810f92d2449a721685b72ff7c8330/lateximg_large.png","width":997},"regular":{"height":174,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/16/e69522ec2461ca14fd0f2cca3367b4ee/901810f92d2449a721